			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><hr /></td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Great post.  I'll just add another situation where you can use root to pull.
<br />

<br />
Linked Mobs - as you get into the higher 20's and 30's, you will find that pulling with a bow or other ranged spell doesn't work so often.  The mobs are linked.  <img src="images/smiles/icon_sad.gif" alt="icon_sad.gif" border="0" />   So if you attack one at the camp, the entire camp will come for you.  Deathifst and cyclops (by the gate) are like this.  Usually, the puller has to pull by proximity, thereby entering the aggro range of one MOB without getting too close to the others.
<br />

<br />
If you have two mobs at a camp, simply root one of them and have the tank taunt the other one that comes.  Depending on how long it takes you to kill the first MOB, the second one should still be standing there waiting for you.
<br />

<br />
This strategy also works at three or four mob camps as long as your group can handle the entire camp less one rooted MOB at one time.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
